                     <author>Muḥammad ʻAlī al-Ḥusainīمحمد علی الحسینی
                        
                        
                        
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Majmaʻ al-ṭuyūr</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">یخچالیه</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>An ethical miscellany in prose and verse after the style of the<title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Gulistān (<foreign xml:lang="fa">گلستان</foreign>)</title>. The book is divided into five chapters called āshyānah, each of which is further subdivided into sections called parvāz</note>
                     <note>This work, of which the present may be a unique copy, was composed during the reign of<persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc"
                                  type="alt"
                                  ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/59940176"
                                  key="no98106664">Shāh ʻAbbas II (<date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" from="1642" to="1667">1052-1077</date>)</persName>(see<locus n="116a">fol. 116a</locus>), and therefore this manuscript, of which unfortunately the first folio is missing, must have been written during the author's lifetime</note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>For a more detailed description see Arberry 1939, page 387.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
